[2026-06-28]
## RR Day 41 — Advanced Pipelines, Combining All Tools

### Completed
- Built a multi-tool pipeline against a live NOC log (noc.log)
- Extracted CRIT events with grep, pulled IPs with awk
- Counted repeat offenders using sort | uniq -c | sort -rn
- Wrapped final output in a formatted report using awk BEGIN/END
- Debugged pipeline order — identified why sort must come before uniq
- Identified why awk sits at the end of the pipeline not the middle

### Key Concepts
- Pipes pass streams not files — each tool is blind to what came before it
- Unix philosophy: text in, text out, chain forever
- sort before uniq is always required — uniq only collapses adjacent duplicates
- sort appears twice in the same pipeline for different reasons:
  first to group duplicates, second to rank by count
- Removing the first sort silently breaks uniq on large datasets
- awk BEGIN/END wraps any pipeline output in a report without touching the data
- -F is only needed when the delimiter is not a space

