[2026-06-23]
## RR Day 39 — tr Command, Character Translation

### Completed
- Translated character ranges with tr 'A-Z' 'a-z' and tr 'a-z' 'A-Z'
- Replaced delimiters using tr ':' ' ' — colon to whitespace
- Distinguished -d (delete) from -s (squeeze) by reading live output
- Ran ip neigh show and analyzed a live ARP table on the VM
- Identified gateway entry, MAC address, and neighbor states from raw output
- Connected fe80:: link-local IPv6 to its IPv4 equivalent (169.254.0.0/16)

### Key Concepts
- tr operates at character level — no regex, no patterns, no field awareness
- -d removes the character entirely from the stream
- -s squeezes consecutive duplicate characters down to one — not deletion
- tr lane: fastest way to normalize case or clean spacing before piping to awk
- ip neigh show is a layer 2 diagnostic — ping says unreachable, neighbor
  table says why (REACHABLE / STALE / FAILED)
- STALE = known device, not recently confirmed — not broken, just quiet
- FAILED = ARP went unanswered — device down or MAC changed
- fe80:: is IPv6 link-local — never routes, stays on the link only
- Same physical device can hold routable IPv4 and link-local IPv6 simultaneously
- Gateway reachability state check identified as Day 47 health-check
  script foundation

