- Used -i flag to edit file in-place:
  sed -i.bak 's/DISABLED/ENABLED/' sed.reps
- Confirmed .bak backup file created automatically

### Key Concepts
- sed = Stream Editor — reads line by line,
  substitutes patterns on the way through
- Syntax: sed 's/old/new/' file
  three slashes required — missing the last one
  causes "unterminated s command" error
- Default behavior: output to screen, file unchanged
- -i edits the file in-place
- -i.bak creates a backup before overwriting —
  always use in production environments
- Real world use: change config file values without
  opening a text editor, scriptable across servers

