[2026-06-15]
## RR Day 36 — awk Arithmetic and Counters

### Completed
- Filtered users by UID >= 1000: 
  awk -F: '$3 >= 1000 {print $1, $3}'
- Summed all UIDs using += accumulator:
  awk -F: '{sum += $3} END {print "Total:", sum}'
- Counted total lines using NR built-in variable
- Built combined report — filter + count + summary:
  '$3 >= 1000 {print $1, $3; sum++} 
  END {print "Total Users:", sum}'

### Key Concepts
- >= means greater than or equal to — plain math,
  no quotes, no regex
- += adds to a running total each line
- ++ increments a counter by 1 — shorthand for += 1
- NR = Number of Records — total lines processed
- Custom counter only increments when pattern matches
  NR counts everything regardless of pattern
- Semicolon separates multiple statements in one
  action block
- END fires once after all lines are processed

