## RR Day 33: sort + uniq — Top Events Report

### Completed
- Built 4-stage pipeline to surface top repeated log events:
  journalctl | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn | head -20
- Saved output to top_events_report.txt using > redirect
- Discovered sshd_gate.sh output visible in system journal

### Key Concepts
- sort reorders lines alphabetically — identical lines 
  become adjacent as a side effect
- uniq -c only counts adjacent duplicates — sort must 
  come first or counts are wrong
- sort -rn: -n treats values as numbers not text,
  -r reverses so highest count appears first
- head -20 shows first 20 lines — top of a reverse 
  sorted list = highest counts
- > creates a new file and redirects output into it —
  terminal output disappears, files persist

