## Day 31 — Memory Drill + Username Extraction

### Completed
- Rebuilt IP extraction pipeline from memory:
  journalctl -u sshd | grep -v '0.0.0.0' | 
  grep -oE '[0-9]{1,3}\.[0-9]{1,3}\.[0-9]{1,3}\.[0-9]{1,3}'
- Extended pipeline to extract usernames from SSH logs:
  journalctl -u sshd | grep -oE 'for [^ ]+ from' | 
  grep -oE '[^ ]+' | grep -v 'for\|from'

### Key Concepts
- * matches zero or more — can return empty strings
- + matches one or more — requires at least one character
- [^ ]+ splits on spaces, carving out individual words
- \| is the OR operator in basic regex
- In -E mode you write | without the backslash
- Always quote regex patterns — unquoted patterns get
  interpreted by the shell before grep sees them

